
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <title>Buttons Collection</title>
</head>

<style>
    body {
        margin: 10px;
        padding: 10px;
    }

    img {
        height: 250px;

    }

    .youtube-btn {
        background-color: rgb(196, 32, 32);
        color: white;
        border-width: 0px;
        height: 36px;
        width: 90px;
        border-radius: 2px;
        cursor: pointer;
        transition: background-color 2s;
    }

    .youtube-btn:hover {
        /* opacity: 0.8; (for elements) */
        background-color: rgba(196, 32, 32, 0.7);
    }

    .youtube-btn:active {
        opacity: 0.5;
    }

    .youtube-btn:focus {
        background-color: green;
    }


    .padding-yt-btn {
        background-color: rgb(196, 32, 32);
        color: white;
        border-width: 0px;
        /* height: 36px;
        width: 90px; */
        padding-top: 10px;
        padding-bottom: 10px;
        padding-left: 12px;
        padding-right: 12px;
        border-radius: 2px;
        cursor: pointer;
    }




    .join-btn {
        height: 36px;
        width: 70px;
        color: rgb(50, 126, 197);
        background-color: white;
        border-color: rgb(50, 126, 197);
        border-style: solid;
        border-width: 1px;
        border-radius: 2px;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .tweet-btn {
        background-color: rgb(48, 131, 225);
        color: white;
        border-width: 0;
        font-weight: bold;
        font-size: 0.9em;
        height: 36px;
        width: 70px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .request-btn {
        background-color: black;
        color: white;
        height: 36px;
        width: 90px;
        font-size: 12px;
        border-width: 0px;
        cursor: pointer;

        transition: opacity 0.5s;
    }

    .request-btn:hover {
        opacity: 0.8;
    }

    .amazon-btn {
        background-color: rgb(255, 216, 20);
        height: 32px;
        width: 180px;
        border-width: 0px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .buy-btn {
        background-color: rgb(255, 164, 28);
        height: 32px;
        width: 90px;
        border-width: 0px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .signup-btn {
        background-color: green;
        height: 36px;
        width: 80px;
        border-width: 0px;
        color: white;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-weight: bold;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .bootstrap-btn {
        background-color: #7354AD;
        color: white;
        height: 36px;
        width: 90px;
        border-width: 0px;
        border-radius: 2px;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .bootstrap-download-btn {
        height: 36px;
        width: 90px;
        color: rgb(108, 117, 125);
        background-color: white;
        border-color: rgb(108, 117, 125);
        border-style: solid;
        border-width: 1px;
        border-radius: 2px;
        cursor: pointer;

        transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s;
    }

    .bootstrap-download-btn:hover {
        background-color: #6C747B;
        color: white;
    }

    .linkdin-btn {
        background-color: rgb(10, 102, 194);
        color: white;
        height: 32px;
        width: 220px;
        border-width: 0px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .save-btn {
        height: 36px;
        width: 70px;
        color: rgb(50, 126, 197);
        background-color: white;
        border-color: rgb(50, 126, 197);
        border-style: solid;
        border-width: 1.5px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        font-weight: bold;
        cursor: pointer;

        transition: background-color 0.5s;
    }

    .save-btn:hover {
        /* opacity: 0.1; brightens the whole element, so dont use this */
        background-color: rgba(50, 126, 197, 0.1);
    }
</style>

<body>
    <h1>Default Border Settings</h1>
    <img src="default-btn-box-model.png" alt="">
    <br>
    <button>Button</button>


    <h2>Examples of Buttons</h2>

    <!-- YouTube Button -->
    <button class="youtube-btn">
        Subscribe
    </button>

    <!-- Join Button -->
    <button class="join-btn">
        JOIN
    </button>

    <!-- Tweet button -->
    <button class="tweet-btn">
        Tweet
    </button>

    <br> <br>

    <!-- Uber Request Button -->
    <button class="request-btn">
        Request Now
    </button>

    <!-- Amazon "Add to cart" button -->
    <button class="amazon-btn">
        Add to Cart
    </button>
    <button class="buy-btn">Buy Now</button>

    <br><br>

    <!-- Sign Up Button -->
    <button class="signup-btn">
        Sign Up
    </button>

    <br><br>

    <!-- Bootstrap Buttons -->
    <button class="bootstrap-btn">Get Started</button>
    <button class="bootstrap-download-btn">
        Download
    </button>

    <br><br>

    <!-- Linkden Buttons -->
    <button class="linkdin-btn">
        Apply on Company Website
    </button>
    <button class="save-btn">
        Save
    </button>

    <!-- Challenges area -->

    <h2>Challenges</h2>

    <style>
        .challenge {
            background-color: green;
            color: white;
            border-color: green;
            border-style: solid;
            border-radius: 2px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .stretch-btn{
            padding: 8px 16px;

            transition: padding 1s;
        }
        .stretch-btn:hover {
            padding: 16px 32px;
        }

        .shadow-btn{
            padding: 8px 16px;

            box-shadow: 4px 4px 2px rgba(0,0,0, 0.2);
            transition: box-shadow 1s;
        }
        .shadow-btn:hover{
            margin-left: 2px;
            margin-top: 2px;
            box-shadow: none;
        }

        .padding-btns{
         padding: 8px 12px;
         transition: padding 0.4s;
        }
        .padding-btns:hover{
            padding-left: 18px;
            padding-right: 18px;
        }
    </style>

    <button class="stretch-btn challenge">Stretch</button>
    <br><br>
    <button class="shadow-btn challenge">Shadow</button>
    <br><br>
    <button class="padding-btns challenge">One</button>
    <button class="padding-btns challenge">Two</button>
    <button class="padding-btns challenge">Three</button>

    <h2>
        Points:
    </h2>
    <p>1. Padding are better alternative for buttons, coz adding text to buttons that has heights and widths overflows,
        while if only padding is set for the button, the content of element doesn't overflow, but rather adjusts itself.
    </p>
    <p>Example:</p>
    <!-- YouTube Button -->
    <button class="youtube-btn" style="vertical-align: ;">
        Subscribe Here
    </button>
    <!-- YouTube Button -->
    <button class="padding-yt-btn">
        Subscribe Here NOW how are you doing!
    </button>

    <p>2. The alignment of buttons (elements) is based on text, so that's why they appear weird rn. </p>
    <p>3. Add transitions to the "base css style element", not psuedo classes.
    </p>
